    featuredImage: "https://cttruckshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Screenshot-2023-09-28-at-19.48.38.jpg",
    metaDescription: "Get answers to frequently asked questions about semi towing services. Learn when to call, costs, and what to expect from professional towing.",
    content: "<h1>Semi Towing Frequently Asked Questions</h1><p>Your Comprehensive Guide to Semi-Truck Towing</p><p>In heavy-duty transportation, semi-trucks are crucial in delivering goods across the country. However, even these mighty vehicles occasionally encounter issues on the road that require the services of a professional semi-truck towing company.</p><img src=\"https://cttruckshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Screenshot-2023-09-28-at-19.48.38.jpg\" alt=\"semi-towing-info\" /><h2>What Is Semi-Truck Towing?</h2><p><a href=\"https://cttruckshop.com/wrecker-heavy-duty-towing-areas/\">Semi-truck towing</a> is a specialized service designed to assist large commercial trucks when they experience breakdowns, accidents, or other roadside emergencies.</p><h3>When Should You Call for Semi-Truck Towing?</h3><p><em>1. Breakdowns:</em> If your semi-truck experiences a mechanical failure or engine breakdown, it is essential to call for semi-truck towing immediately.</p><p><em>2. Accidents:</em> In the unfortunate event of a collision or accident involving a semi-truck, it is crucial to contact a professional towing service.</p><p><em>3. Fuel Issues:</em> Running out of fuel on the road can leave you stranded. A semi-truck towing service can deliver fuel to get you back on your way.</p><h3>How Much Does Semi-Truck Towing Cost?</h3><p>The cost of semi-truck towing can vary depending on several factors, including the distance to be towed, the type of towing required, and the time of day. On average, you can expect to pay between $300 and $600 for a standard tow.</p><p>For reliable <a href=\"https://cttruckshop.com/semi-towing-services/\">semi-truck towing services</a> in Phoenix, AZ, contact CT Truck and Trailer Shop today.</p>"
